Download logo Eritrea through the Eritrean Embassy in Egypt participated at the 54thÂ Cairo Book Fair.  The Book Fair that was staged at the International Exhibition Center was officially opened by Mr. Moustafa Madbouly, Prime Minister of Egypt and Dr. Neveen Al-Kilany, Minister of Culture. Eritrea displayed books depicting the history, geographical location, natural resources and tourist attractions of Eritrea as well as the culture and diversity of the Eritrean people. At the Book Fair, Mr. Fasil Gebreselasie, Eritrean Ambassador to Egypt, gave a briefing to the senior officials that visited the Eritrean pavilion. Distributed by APO Group on behalf of Ministry of Information, Eritrea.